# Google Sheets Configuration
# Get this from Google Cloud Console > Service Accounts
# Format: {"type":"service_account","project_id":"...","private_key_id":"..."}
GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT={"type":"service_account","project_id":"your-project","private_key_id":"...","private_key":"-----BEGIN PRIVATE KEY-----\n...\n-----END PRIVATE KEY-----\n","client_email":"your-service-account@your-project.iam.gserviceaccount.com","client_id":"...","auth_uri":"https://accounts.google.com/o/oauth2/auth","token_uri":"https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token","auth_provider_x509_cert_url":"https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v1/certs","client_x509_cert_url":"https://www.googleapis.com/robot/v1/metadata/x509/..."}

# Your Google Sheet ID (from the URL)
# Example: https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/YOUR_SHEET_ID_HERE/edit
SHEET_ID=your_google_sheet_id_here

# The Grid ID (GID) of your Signups sheet
# Find this by clicking on the Signups tab and checking the URL:
# https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/SHEET_ID/edit#gid=SIGNUPS_GID_HERE
# Usually 0 for first sheet, 1 for second sheet, etc.
SIGNUPS_GID=0

# ============================================================================
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ============================================================================

# 1. Create a Google Sheet with two tabs:
#    
#    a) "Slots" tab with columns (A-E):
#       - A: Date (e.g., "2024-12-01")
#       - B: Slot Label (e.g., "9:00 AM - 10:00 AM")
#       - C: Capacity (e.g., 10)
#       - D: Taken (e.g., 0)
#       - E: Notes (optional)
#    
#    b) "Signups" tab with columns (A-I):
#       - A: Timestamp
#       - B: Date
#       - C: Slot Label
#       - D: Name
#       - E: Email
#       - F: Phone
#       - G: Notes
#       - H: Slot Row ID
#       - I: Status (ACTIVE or CANCELLED:timestamp)

# 2. Create a Google Cloud Project:
#    - Go to https://console.cloud.google.com/
#    - Create a new project or select existing
#    - Enable Google Sheets API
#    - Create a Service Account
#    - Download JSON credentials
#    - Copy the entire JSON as the value for GOOGLE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT

# 3. Share your Google Sheet:
#    - Open your Google Sheet
#    - Click "Share" button
#    - Add the service account email (from the JSON, "client_email" field)
#    - Give it "Editor" access

# 4. Get Sheet ID:
#    - Open your Google Sheet
#    - Copy the ID from URL: docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/SHEET_ID/edit

# 5. Get Signups GID:
#    - Click on the "Signups" tab
#    - Check URL: #gid=SIGNUPS_GID
#    - Copy that number

# 6. Deploy to Vercel:
#    - Go to your Vercel project settings
#    - Navigate to Environment Variables
#    - Add these three variables
#    - Redeploy your project

# ============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ============================================================================

# ⚠️ NEVER commit the actual .env file to git!
# ⚠️ NEVER expose these values in client-side code!
# ⚠️ Keep your service account JSON secure!
# ⚠️ Regularly rotate your service account keys!
# ⚠️ Use Vercel's environment variables for production!
